{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"mucky-like-elkhound","description":"## What\n\nAdd a lightweight CI gate that keeps the docs index honest: every living top-level\n`docs/*.md` page must be linked from the central index (`docs/README.md`), with an\nexplicit allowlist for intentionally-unindexed files (git-ignored `*.local.md`,\nhistorical/archive docs). This drift-proofs the P2 index-completeness finding so it\ncannot silently recur. Optionally also flag obviously-dead relative markdown links.\n\nTemplate the established pattern: `scripts/gen_env_registry.py` + its CI drift gate\nshow the shape (a small script invoked from `.github/workflows/test.yml` that fails on\ndivergence).\n\n- Add `scripts/check_docs_index.py` (new): enumerate `docs/*.md`, parse links out of\n  `docs/README.md`, diff against an allowlist, exit non-zero on unindexed living docs.\n- Wire it into `.github/workflows/test.yml` as a gating step.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A new script fails when a living top-level `docs/*.md` is not linked from\n      `docs/README.md` and not on the allowlist.\n- [ ] The allowlist covers `*.local.md` and designated historical/archive docs.\n- [ ] The check is wired into CI and passes on the (now-completed) index.\n- [ ] Adding a new unindexed doc is demonstrably caught (note manual verification).\n\nFiles: `scripts/check_docs_index.py` (new), `.github/workflows/test.yml`.","id":"f088-ef68-9518-4833","parent_id":"4191-b4f9-146a-43cd","priority":2,"tags":["docs","ci","p1"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"P1: Add docs index-completeness / dead-link CI gate"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783814573576292001,"uuid":"894ec476-0780-40dd-bf98-8829010086c8"}